void MMWave_decodeError ( int32_t  errCode,
MMWave_ErrorLevel *  errorLevel,
int16_t *  mmWaveError,
int16_t *  subSysError 
)

Description
Application can use the API to decode the error. The mmWave API can return errors because of either the mmWave or the underlying mmWave Link API.

Parameters
[in]errCodeEncoded error code retreived from the mmWave API. This is the error code which will be decoded.
[out]errorLevelError level populated by the API.
[out]mmWaveErrorError code from the mmWave module. This could be set to 0 to indicate that the mmWave module did not return an error.
[out]subSysErrorSubsystem error code. This could be set to 0 to indicate that there was no error at the subsystem level.
Return values
Notapplicable

int32_t MMWave_getBpmChirpHandle ( MMWave_Handle  mmWaveHandle,
uint32_t  bpmChirpIndex,
MMWave_BpmChirpHandle *  bpmChirpHandle,
int32_t *  errCode 
)

Description
The function can be used by the application to get the BPM cfg handle at the specified index. If the index exceeds the number of BPM configurations the function will fail with the error code.

Parameters
[in]mmWaveHandleHandle to the mmWave module
[in]bpmChirpIndexBPM cfg index for which the handle is needed. Set to 1 to get the first BPM configuration index, etc
[out]bpmChirpHandlePopulated BPM Cfg handle
[out]errCodeEncoded Error code populated by the API on an error
Return values
Success- 0
Error- <0

int32_t MMWave_open ( MMWave_Handle  mmWaveHandle,
const MMWave_OpenCfg *  ptrOpenCfg,
rlCalibrationData_t *  ptrCalibData,
int32_t *  errCode 
)

Description
The function is used to open the mmWave module.

Parameters
[in]mmWaveHandleHandle to the mmWave module
[in]ptrOpenCfgPointer to the open configuration
[in]ptrCalibDataThis is the pointer to the calibration data which is passed to the BSS to bypass calibration and restore it to a previously saved value. Set this to NULL and the mmWave module will request the BSS to perform the calibration.
[out]errCodeEncoded Error code populated by the API on an error
Precondition
MMWave_init
MMWave_sync
Return values
Success- 0
Error- <0

int32_t MMWave_sync ( MMWave_Handle  mmWaveHandle,
int32_t *  errCode 
)

Description
The function is used to synchronize the execution of the control module between the execution domains. Applications are recommended to invoke the function until the "sync" is acheived. Failure to do so will result in the mmWave module misbehaving.

Parameters
[in]mmWaveHandleHandle to the mmWave control module
[out]errCodeEncoded Error code populated by the API on an error
Return values
Synchronized- 1
Unsynchronized- 0
Error- <0
